##Question 6 Focus only on the rows where log-earth radius and log-period have no missing values, and perform kmeans with four clusters on these two columns.

##Question 7 Add the clustering labels to the dataset through a new factor column called type, with levels rocky, hot_jupiters, cold_gas_giants, others; similarly to https: //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exoplanet#/media/File:ExoplanetPopulations-20170616. png and produce the scatterplot highlighting these clusters

exo_kmeans = exo_kmeans %>%
  mutate(type = km$cluster,
  type = case_when(
           type == 1 ~ "cold_gas_giants",
           type == 2 ~ "others",
           type == 3 ~ "Rocky",
           type == 4 ~ "hot_jupiters")%>%
           as.factor()%>%
           structure(levels=c("rocky", "hot_jupiters", "cold_gas_giants", "others")))
ggplot(exo_kmeans,aes(x=period,y=earth_radius,color = type))+geom_point()

##Question 9 Transform r_asc and decl into two new variables that are the same varibales but in values of seconds. Use these as coordinates to represent a celestial map for the exoplanets.

# conver r_asc to seconds and save as r_asc_sec
exo$r_asc <- gsub(" ", ":", exo$r_asc, fixed=TRUE) # convert to hh:mm:ss
exo$r_asc <- hms(exo$r_asc) 
## Warning in .parse_hms(..., order = "HMS", quiet = quiet): Some strings failed to
## parse, or all strings are NAs
exo$r_asc_sec <- period_to_seconds(exo$r_asc)
# convert Declination to seconds and save as decl_sec
exo$decl <- gsub(" ", ":", exo$decl, fixed=TRUE) # convert to dd:mm:ss, where dd=3600ss
exo$decl <- hms(exo$decl) # for Decl, dd is similar to hh where :=3600ss
## Warning in .parse_hms(..., order = "HMS", quiet = quiet): Some strings failed to
## parse, or all strings are NAs
exo$decl_sec <- period_to_seconds(exo$decl)

ggplot(exo, aes(r_asc_sec, decl_sec, color= factor(meth))) +

##Question 10 Create an animated time series where multiple lines illustrate the evolution over time of the total number of exoplanets discovered for each method up to that year.

exo_ts <-exo %>%
           group_by(meth, year) %>%  
           summarise(Count = length(meth)) %>%
           mutate(Count = cumsum(Count))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'meth' (override with `.groups` argument)
exo_ts <-na.omit(exo_ts)
ggplot(exo_ts, aes(x = year, y = Count, group = meth)) + 
      geom_line(aes(color = meth)) + 
    geom_point(size = 2) + 
    transition_reveal(year) + 
  labs(title = 'Total number of exoplanets discovered for each method',x='year',y = 'Count')

##Question 12 Fit a linear regression model where log period is the response variable and the logs of host_mass, host_temp and axis are the covariates (exclude rows that contain at least one missing value). Include an intercept term in the regression model.

exo_lm = exo %>%
  filter(!is.na(period))%>%
  filter(!is.na(host_mass))%>%
  filter(!is.na(host_temp))%>%
  filter(!is.na(axis))%>%
   mutate(log_period = log(period),
     log_host_mass = log(host_mass),
         log_host_temp = log(host_temp),
         log_axis = log(axis),
         na.rm = TRUE)%>%
    select(log_period,log_host_mass,log_host_temp,log_axis)

linearMod = lm(log_period~log_host_mass+log_host_temp+log_axis,data = exo_lm)

##Question 13 Include in your R Markdown document some model summaries and an interpretation of the model you have ﬁt.
